(birds chirping)
旅店主人克拉克夫人

57
00:04:17,089 --> 00:04:18,283
Mike: Mrs. Clark, the proprietor,
从她接手旅店后

58
00:04:18,324 --> 00:04:19,985
says she hasn't slept a night

59
00:04:20,026 --> 00:04:22,859
since acquiring the inn and I believe her.
她就没睡过觉 我相信她

60
00:04:22,895 --> 00:04:25,227
No no no, I pity her.
不，不，我可怜她

61
00:04:25,264 --> 00:04:27,926
But in any case, the eggs Benedict are delicious
但是他们的荷包蛋土司太好吃了

62
00:04:27,967 --> 00:04:30,094
and if you call in advance, Mrs. Clark says
如果你提前电话预约 克拉克夫人说…

63
00:04:30,136 --> 00:04:33,697
she will bake her famous flourless chocolate cake.
…她还会烤制最拿手的巧克力蛋糕

64
00:04:33,739 --> 00:04:37,732
On a Shiver Scale, I award the Weeping Beach Inn six skulls.
就恐怖指数而言 我给垂榉旅馆６颗骷髅头

65
00:04:41,280 --> 00:04:42,872
Screw 'em, five skulls.
见鬼去吧，５颗骷髅头

66
00:04:42,915 --> 00:04:44,405
(truck horn blares)

67
00:04:44,450 --> 00:04:46,543
(traffic noise)
["10座闹鬼旅馆"]

68
00:04:54,827 --> 00:04:57,125
- Hi. - Oh hey.
- 嗨 - 嗨

69
00:04:57,163 --> 00:04:59,825
How's it going? Can I help you?
有什么事吗？

70
00:04:59,865 --> 00:05:01,298
Yeah, I'm here for the big event.
我是来参加特别活动的

71
00:05:01,334 --> 00:05:05,100
All right. Cool.
哦，好啊

72
00:05:05,137 --> 00:05:06,468
I'm Mike Enslin.
我是麦克・安斯林

73
00:05:06,505 --> 00:05:08,598
Sorry?
谁？

74
00:05:09,976 --> 00:05:11,341
- Book signing. - Oh, right.
- 签名售书 - 哦，是这样啊

75
00:05:11,377 --> 00:05:14,835
Oh, that's you, yeah. I see the resemblance, yeah.
对啊，那人就是你 和照片上还挺象的

76
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:16,939
- That's a good picture. - Thanks, man.
- 照片照的不错 - 多谢夸奖

77
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:18,541
All right, hold on.
好的，等一下

78
00:05:18,584 --> 00:05:21,712
Um... attention, book lovers.
请注意，书迷朋友们

79
00:05:21,754 --> 00:05:25,212
Tonight we have noted occult writer
今晚著名鬼故事作家

80
00:05:25,257 --> 00:05:27,088
Michael Enslin
麦克・安斯林

81
00:05:27,126 --> 00:05:29,856
at the Author's Corner tonight.
将莅临作家角

82
00:05:29,895 --> 00:05:33,160
He's the writer of the best-selling ghost survival guides,
他是畅销小说 ＂鬼魂生存指南＂的作者

83
00:05:33,199 --> 00:05:36,532
um... with such titles as "10 Haunted Hotels,"
他的作品包括： ＂１０家鬼店＂

84
00:05:36,569 --> 00:05:39,697
"10 Haunted Graveyards,"
＂１０座鬼坟＂

85
00:05:39,739 --> 00:05:41,297
"10 Haunted Lighthouses."
＂１０座闹鬼灯塔＂

86
00:05:41,340 --> 00:05:43,774
That's tonight, 7:00 pm.
签售会将于今晚７：００开始

87
00:05:43,809 --> 00:05:46,073
Mike: Anyway, so I really enjoyed writing it,
总之，写作令我乐在其中

88
00:05:46,112 --> 00:05:48,046
and that's kind of a history of the book.
这些作品本身也是在讲述历史

89
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:51,174
And I hope you enjoy it, or enjoyed it.
希望你们都能喜欢

90
00:05:51,217 --> 00:05:53,708
Uh, you know, stay scared.
永远保持恐惧

91
00:05:53,753 --> 00:05:55,152
Right? Any questions?
有什么问题吗？

92
00:05:55,187 --> 00:05:57,485
Where's the scariest place you've ever been?
你去过的最恐怖的地方是哪儿？

93
00:05:57,523 --> 00:05:59,650
Scariest place I've ever been?
我去过的最恐怖的地方？

94
00:05:59,692 --> 00:06:01,683
Uh, I've never heard that question before.
这问题以前还真没人问过我

95
00:06:01,727 --> 00:06:03,922
- That's a joke. - (chuckles)
我开玩笑的

96
00:06:03,963 --> 00:06:06,295
Well, all these places have very colorful histories.
每个地方都有自己鲜明的特点

97
00:06:06,332 --> 00:06:07,890
Um...

98
00:06:07,933 --> 00:06:10,026
I would say, if I had to pick a top one,
如果真要叫我选个最恐怖的

99
00:06:10,069 --> 00:06:12,060
I would say Bar Harbor,
我想应该是 巴尔海港吧

100
00:06:12,104 --> 00:06:15,130
the site of the grisly McTeig wedding night murders.
恐怖的麦德新婚之夜 谋杀案的案发现场

101
00:06:15,174 --> 00:06:17,870
That's an intense place. Or maybe St. Cloud, Minnesota,
那儿真是个恐怖的地方 或者是圣・克劳德，明尼苏达

102
00:06:17,910 --> 00:06:20,811
where the crazed war widow threw her baby down a well.
在那里，那些在战争中失去丈夫的寡妇 失去理智的把婴儿扔到井里

103
00:06:20,846 --> 00:06:23,178
I mean, those all have a lot of... I mean, it's thick.
那些地方 都弥漫着恐怖的气息

104
00:06:23,215 --> 00:06:26,013
- The air is thick. - What about poltergeists?
- 很浓的气息 - 那些搞恶作剧的鬼呢？

105
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:28,919
Look, I'm a good researcher. I go into every gig locked and loaded.
我是个专业的研究者 我每到一处都是装备精良

106
00:06:28,954 --> 00:06:32,185
I travel with an EMF meter, full-range spectrometer,
我带着电磁辐射仪 全波光谱仪

107
00:06:32,224 --> 00:06:34,920
infrared camera. I mean, look, nothing would make me happier
红外照相机，我最大的乐趣…

108
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:36,894
than to experience a paranormal event,
…就是去检验那些异灵事件

109
00:06:36,929 --> 00:06:39,659
you know, to get a glimpse of the elusive light
就如同黑暗中瞥见

110
00:06:39,699 --> 00:06:41,064
at the end of the tunnel.
一缕神光般欣喜若狂

111
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:42,931
(thunder crashes)

112
00:06:42,968 --> 00:06:45,266
So you're saying there's no such thing as ghosts?
你是说根本就不存在什么鬼魂？

113
00:06:46,405 --> 00:06:48,066
I'm saying I've never seen one,
我是说目前为止我还没见过

114
00:06:48,107 --> 00:06:50,473
but they're awful convenient for desperate hotels
但是对那些生意惨淡的旅店来说

115
00:06:50,509 --> 00:06:52,704
- when the interstate moves away. - (knocking)
这些传闻却无疑会给他们带来生意

116
00:06:52,745 --> 00:06:55,441
This thing has really gone off the rails. Who has a pen?
扯的太远了，谁有笔？

117
00:06:55,481 --> 00:06:58,041
- I do. - Which one?
- 我有 - 要签在哪本书上？

118
00:06:58,084 --> 00:07:01,315
Uh, but seriously, Mike, if I want to see a real live ghost,
说真的，麦克 要想见真正的鬼魂　

119
00:07:01,353 --> 00:07:03,116
where's my best bet?
最好去什么地方？

120
00:07:03,155 --> 00:07:04,452
- Guaranteed? - Yeah.
- 一定要看到？ - 恩

121
00:07:04,490 --> 00:07:06,048
Haunted Mansion, Orlando.
奥兰多的闹鬼公寓

122
00:07:06,092 --> 00:07:08,287
Awesome, thanks.
太棒了，多谢

123
00:07:09,295 --> 00:07:10,887
- Stay scared. - Thank you.
- 时刻保持恐惧 - 谢谢

124
00:07:10,930 --> 00:07:12,761
Cashier: Hey, Ray, can you lock up?
雷，你晚上锁门，好吗？

125
00:07:12,798 --> 00:07:15,733
I got band practice tonight.
我今晚要去乐队训练

126
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:17,395
Holy shit.
天啊

127
00:07:17,436 --> 00:07:18,926
What rock did you find that under?
［漫漫回家路 作者：麦克・安斯林］

128
00:07:17,436 --> 00:07:18,926
这书你是从哪儿找到的？

129
00:07:18,971 --> 00:07:20,996
- Um, eBay. - EBay, huh?
- 易趣网 - 易趣？

130
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:23,065
- (girl laughs) - How much did it go for?
你多少钱买的？

131
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:25,634
Well, there weren't many bidders.
没多少人竞买

132
00:07:25,678 --> 00:07:28,112
I would think not.
大概一个都没吧

133
00:07:28,147 --> 00:07:31,116
- Wow. - But it's, um...
- 哇 - 这是本…

134
00:07:31,150 --> 00:07:32,879
- an amazing book. - Oh.
- …很出色的书 - 噢

135
00:07:32,918 --> 00:07:35,682
Um, so... unique
非常…独特

136
00:07:35,721 --> 00:07:38,656
and inspirational and honest.
…极具灵感 语言诚恳

137
00:07:38,691 --> 00:07:40,386
Thanks. What's your name?
谢谢 你叫什么名字？

138
00:07:40,426 --> 00:07:42,451
- Um, Anna. - Okay, Anna.
- 安娜 - 好的，安娜

139
00:07:42,495 --> 00:07:44,588
Are you gonna write another one like this one?
你还会再写类似风格的作品吗？

140
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:46,461
Nah, it's a different guy.
不会了

141
00:07:46,499 --> 00:07:48,467
Um...

142
00:07:48,501 --> 00:07:50,469
- can I ask you a question? - Sure.
- 能问你个问题吗？ - 当然了

143
00:07:50,503 --> 00:07:53,836
Um, the relationship in the book
这本书里所描写的父子关系…

144
00:07:53,873 --> 00:07:56,569
with the father and the son... it's probably too personal,
这问题可能太私人化了

145
00:07:56,609 --> 00:08:00,204
- but, um, it's so authentic and... - Mm-hm.
但是，写的情感真挚…

146
00:08:00,246 --> 00:08:02,806
Well-constructed, and...
…而且构思巧妙…

147
00:08:02,848 --> 00:08:05,749
is it true?
…是真实的故事吗？

148
00:08:05,785 --> 00:08:08,413
No.
不

149
00:08:08,454 --> 00:08:10,615
Well, thank you for this. I really appreciate it.
谢谢，真太感谢您了

150
00:08:10,656 --> 00:08:12,021
My pleasure.
不胜荣幸

151
00:08:12,057 --> 00:08:13,615
Bye.
再见

152
00:08:22,701 --> 00:08:24,669
(dog barks)

153
00:08:30,075 --> 00:08:32,509
- Man: Good boy! - Man #2: Yo, homey...
- 好孩子！ - 真舒服…

154
00:08:32,545 --> 00:08:34,672
Woman: Just a minute, Tiffany!
等一会儿，蒂凡尼！

155
00:08:34,713 --> 00:08:36,977
Yeah, I'm just gonna tie it inside my suit here.
我正准备把它系在我衣服里

156
00:09:08,614 --> 00:09:11,310
(airplane buzzes)

157
00:09:35,674 --> 00:09:37,665
Man: Yo, Greg, check him out!
嘿，格瑞，快去看看

158
00:09:37,710 --> 00:09:39,439
Woman: Did you see what happened?
刚才你看到没？

159
00:09:39,478 --> 00:09:41,343
Oh yeah.
是的

160
00:09:42,715 --> 00:09:45,206
Are you okay, buddy?
老兄，你还好吗？

161
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:48,243
