00:10:19,184 --> 00:10:22,153
I read your last book... the "10 Haunted Mansions" thing.
我读了你的最新小说 那本关于10座闹鬼庄园的

174
00:10:22,187 --> 00:10:23,779
Man, that's some scary shit.
可真够可怕的

175
00:10:23,822 --> 00:10:26,120
Cool.
不错

176
00:10:26,158 --> 00:10:27,785
Later on, dude.
回头见，老兄

177
00:10:27,826 --> 00:10:31,557
(soft rock playing)

178
00:10:31,597 --> 00:10:33,189
- Hi. - Hi, how you doing?
- 嗨 - 嗨，最近还好吧？

179
00:10:33,232 --> 00:10:35,393
- Hi. - Good.
- 嗨 - 很好

180
00:10:35,434 --> 00:10:37,265
Thanks.
谢谢

181
00:10:42,841 --> 00:10:45,833
(customers chatting)

182
00:10:52,766 --> 00:10:53,366
[你真是太棒了！]

183
00:10:53,367 --> 00:10:55,367
[麦克：生日快乐 天天开心  --大卫]

184
00:11:07,368 --> 00:11:09,368
[不要进入1408]

185
00:11:24,149 --> 00:11:25,946
That's cute.
真有趣

186
00:11:25,985 --> 00:11:29,182
Woman: Good evening, Dolphin Hotel.
晚上好，海豚酒店

187
00:11:29,221 --> 00:11:30,745
How might I direct your call?
竭诚为您服务

188
00:11:30,789 --> 00:11:32,654
Mike: Yeah, hi, I'm calling about room 1408.
我想问下１４０８房间

189
00:11:32,691 --> 00:11:34,454
One moment please, sir.
请稍等，先生

190
00:11:36,495 --> 00:11:37,826
Man: How may I help you?
请问有什么需要吗？

191
00:11:37,863 --> 00:11:40,354
Yeah, I'd like to stay in room 1408 please.
我想预定１４０８房间

192
00:11:40,399 --> 00:11:43,857
That room is unavailable, sir.
那房间不能入住，先生

193
00:11:43,902 --> 00:11:46,234
I didn't tell you which date.
我并没有告诉你要哪天入住啊

194
00:11:48,107 --> 00:11:49,506
How about Saturday?
那周六呢？

195
00:11:49,541 --> 00:11:51,304
It's unavailable.
不能入住

196
00:11:53,445 --> 00:11:56,278
(laughs) The following Tuesday?
下周二呢？

197
00:11:56,315 --> 00:11:58,044
Unavailable.
不能入住

198
00:11:58,083 --> 00:11:59,846
Next month?
下个月？

199
00:11:59,885 --> 00:12:01,352
Unavailable.
不能入住

200
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:03,582
Next summer?
那明年夏天呢？

201
00:12:03,622 --> 00:12:05,613
(hangs up)

202
00:12:19,122 --> 00:12:20,913
［工厂业主从酒店窗户跳下］

203
00:12:22,014 --> 00:12:24,014
［１９８３，自杀］

204
00:12:24,615 --> 00:12:25,915
［从酒店窗户跳下］ ［疑影重重的悲剧］

205
00:12:29,548 --> 00:12:32,449
Man: Somebody, anybody, where's good Chinese near 48th?
有人知道４８号街 那儿有什么好吃的中餐吗？

206
00:12:32,484 --> 00:12:34,782
I got to have lunch with that idiot from Random House. Anybody?
我还得和伦敦出版社的 那帮白痴一起吃午饭，有谁知道吗？

207
00:12:34,820 --> 00:12:36,811
Sam, Mike Enslin calling from Los Angeles again.
山姆，麦克・安斯林从洛杉机来的电话

208
00:12:36,855 --> 00:12:39,255
I'll take it in there.
我到里面去接

209
00:12:39,291 --> 00:12:40,724
Clay, you got a sec for Mike Enslin?
克雷，你过来假装我的律师

210
00:12:40,759 --> 00:12:42,226
- Say yes. - Yes.
- 明白了吗？ - 明白

211
00:12:42,261 --> 00:12:44,786
Great. Now look, this guy tends to get a little morose,
太好了，听着 这个家伙脾气不好

212
00:12:44,830 --> 00:12:47,094
so try to keep the energy up. Otherwise he stews in his own funk.
一定要顺着他 否则就不好应付了

213
00:12:47,132 --> 00:12:48,429
- Mike! - Mike: Hey, Sam.
- 麦克！ - 嗨，山姆

214
00:12:48,467 --> 00:12:50,594
Hey hey, read the first five chapters last night.
嗨，我昨晚读了前５章

215
00:12:50,636 --> 00:12:52,263
Spooky shit, couldn't sleep a wink.
太诡异了 吓得都睡不着觉

216
00:12:52,304 --> 00:12:54,238
Great. Hey, did you take care of that thing?
太好了，那件事帮我办了吗？

217
00:12:54,273 --> 00:12:57,242
You'd better believe I did. And I got our top lawyer here right now.
当然了 顶级律师现在就在我旁边

218
00:12:57,276 --> 00:12:58,402
Mike, Clay, Clay, Mike.
麦克，这是克雷 克雷，这是麦克

219
00:12:58,444 --> 00:12:59,672
- Hi, Clay. - Mike.
- 嗨，克雷 - 麦克

220
00:12:59,711 --> 00:13:01,576
Talk fast, all right? This guy's $400 an hour.
有什么问题最好快点问 这家伙一小时要４００呢

221
00:13:01,613 --> 00:13:03,103
All right, Clay, what's up with the Dolphin?
好的，克雷 海豚酒店的事怎么样了？

222
00:13:03,148 --> 00:13:04,547
Yeah, the Dolphin.
是啊，海豚酒店

223
00:13:04,583 --> 00:13:07,143
That stick-up-its-ass relic on Lexington.
莱克星顿大街的那帮蠢货

224
00:13:07,186 --> 00:13:09,211
Too posh for a free plug, right?
干嘛自己给自己找茬呢

225
00:13:09,254 --> 00:13:11,518
Well, you are gonna love what Clay's cooked up.
克雷查到的东西肯定会让你高兴

226
00:13:11,557 --> 00:13:14,082
He dug around and found you... are you sitting down?
他调查了下，找到了… 你坐稳了吗？

227
00:13:14,126 --> 00:13:16,560
- A Federal Civil Rights law.
找到了联邦公民权利法案

228
00:13:16,595 --> 00:13:18,620
Like somebody would discriminate against you,
要是有人歧视你这样富裕的白人 就要涉及这个法案

229
00:13:18,664 --> 00:13:21,758
a well-to-do white guy. But the law's the law, right, Clay?
法律至高无上 对吗，克雷？

230
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,461
Ergo, if the room's not occupied
因此，如果是空房

231
00:13:23,502 --> 00:13:25,470
- they have to give it to you. - Really?
- 他们就必须让你入住 - 真的吗？

232
00:13:25,504 --> 00:13:27,768
Yeah. Now look, the manager there's gonna put up a stink
当然了 听着，那个经理可能会阻挠你

233
00:13:27,806 --> 00:13:29,034
but he knows the drill.
但是规矩他是懂的

234
00:13:29,074 --> 00:13:30,473
- Nothing you can't handle. - So, Mike...
- 所以这事你现在完全能应付 - 那么，麦克

235
00:13:30,509 --> 00:13:32,033
we'll book the room and if they refuse
我们会去预定房间 如果他们拒绝的话

236
00:13:32,077 --> 00:13:33,942
we'll rattle our sabers and file suit.
我们就抗议，并采取法律手段

237
00:13:33,979 --> 00:13:36,447
- So it's all done? - Thanks, Clay. Get lost, all right?
- 这么说都搞定了？ - 谢谢你，克雷，快走吧

238
00:13:36,482 --> 00:13:38,541
Bye, Clay.
再见，克雷

239
00:13:38,584 --> 00:13:40,916
Yeah, Mike, are you there?
麦克，你还在吗？

240
00:13:40,953 --> 00:13:44,320
Yeah, uh, on a more personal note,
现在我们来谈点私人话题

241
00:13:44,356 --> 00:13:45,880
are you sure you want to come here?
你真的决定要回来吗？

242
00:13:45,924 --> 00:13:48,791
Yeah, of course. It'll make a solid closing chapter of the book.
当然了，我要给新书加个精彩的结局

243
00:13:48,827 --> 00:13:51,523
Yeah yeah, I know the routine.
你说的这套我都明白

244
00:13:51,563 --> 00:13:54,555
But, I mean, it's New York.
但是 这里可是纽约

245
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:57,501
All that happened... you really want to put yourself through that?
经历那些变故后 你真的想旧地重游吗？

246
00:13:57,536 --> 00:13:59,834
- I'll be quick. - Are you gonna call Lily?
- 我不会久留的 - 你会给莉莉打电话吗？

247
00:13:59,872 --> 00:14:02,841
No. I don't want to impose.
不，我不想影响她

248
00:14:02,875 --> 00:14:05,969
In and out. Nobody gets hurt.
快去快回，这样对大家都好

249
00:14:07,980 --> 00:14:10,744
It's just a job.
不过是工作罢了

250
00:14:17,122 --> 00:14:19,818
(traffic noise)

251
00:14:21,493 --> 00:14:23,188
Driver: Here you are, Dolphin.
海豚酒店到了

252
00:14:24,730 --> 00:14:26,857
Man: Hey! Taxi!
嗨！的士！

253
00:14:34,072 --> 00:14:36,905
(siren wails)

254
00:14:45,851 --> 00:14:46,018
Woman: It's a beautiful room, with fabulous views of the city.
房间很漂亮 可以看到城市的美景

255
00:14:46,018 --> 00:14:48,418
Woman: It's a beautiful room, with fabulous views of the city.

256
00:14:48,453 --> 00:14:50,045
Pardon me, ladies.
借过，女士

257
00:15:03,502 --> 00:15:04,969
Man: Thanks very much.
非常感谢

258
00:15:05,003 --> 00:15:06,493
Welcome to the Dolphin, sir.
海豚酒店欢迎您，先生

259
00:15:06,538 --> 00:15:08,506
- Are you checking in? - Mike Enslin.
- 您是要登记入住吗？ - 麦克・安斯林

260
00:15:08,540 --> 00:15:09,768
One night.
住一晚

261
00:15:09,808 --> 00:15:12,299
And how are we spelling that today?
请问您的名字怎么拼呢？

262
00:15:12,344 --> 00:15:14,608
- N-S-L-l-N? - N-S-L-l-N.
- N-S-L-l-N? - N-S-L-l-N

263
00:15:14,646 --> 00:15:15,840
Yeah.
对

264
00:15:17,241 --> 00:15:18,841
[客人登记入住前通知经理]

265
00:15:21,420 --> 00:15:23,650
Uh, would you excuse me for a moment, sir?
先生，请您稍等下好吗？

266
00:15:23,689 --> 00:15:25,418
Sure.
没问题

267
00:15:28,527 --> 00:15:31,553
Mr. Dempsey, Mike Enslin's just checked in.
丹普西先生，麦克・安斯林到了

268
00:15:31,597 --> 00:15:34,065
- Where is he? - He's over at my desk.
- 他在哪儿呢？ - 前台接待处那里

269
00:15:34,099 --> 00:15:36,499
That's fine, Marie. I'll take care of it.
好的，玛丽，交给我处理好了

270
00:15:36,535 --> 00:15:37,900
Okay.
好的

271
00:15:43,308 --> 00:15:45,299
It'll just be a minute, Mr. Enslin.
请稍等，安斯林先生

272
00:15:45,344 --> 00:15:47,039
(baby crying)

273
00:15:50,382 --> 00:15:52,714
Good evening, sir. Can I help you with your bag?
晚上好，先生 我来帮你拿行李吧？

274
00:15:52,751 --> 00:15:55,219
- No. - Very well.
- 不用了 - 那好吧

275
00:15:57,122 --> 00:15:59,784
Mr. Enslin, I'm Gerald Olin,
安斯林先生，我是盖瑞德・奥林

276
00:15:59,825 --> 00:16:01,588
manager of the Dolphin.
海豚酒店的经理

277
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:04,562
If there's anything that I can do for you while you're here...
在酒店期间，您的任何要求…

278
00:16:04,596 --> 00:16:06,860
dinner reservations, theater tickets,
无论是预定晚餐，还是演出门票

279
00:16:06,898 --> 00:16:08,627
maybe a Knicks game? Anything...
甚至是尼克斯队比赛门票 都没问题，什么要求都行

280
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:10,658
just tell me. I am at your service.
只要您开口 我竭诚为您服务

281
00:16:10,702 --> 00:16:13,830
Well, if I can just get the key to 1408, I can get out of your hair.
只要给我１４０８房的钥匙 就不会再给你添麻烦了

282
00:16:13,872 --> 00:16:17,603
Oh, we were thinking of upgrading you to a penthouse suite.
我们正打算为您升级到楼顶套房

283
00:16:17,643 --> 00:16:20,168
1408, please.
我只要１４０８房

284
00:16:20,212 --> 00:16:22,339
Insistent, aren't we?
这么坚持？

285
00:16:22,381 --> 00:16:24,246
Could you please humor me
您能不能到我办公室来…

286
00:16:24,283 --> 00:16:28,276
by coming to my office for a more private conversation?
…我们私下好好聊聊呢？

287
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,720
- Sure. - Excellent.
- 没问题 - 好极了

288
00:16:34,826 --> 00:16:37,260
Come in. Make yourself comfortable.
请进，别客气

289
00:16:38,997 --> 00:16:40,828
1408 a smoking room?
１４０８房里允许吸烟吗？

290
00:16:40,866 --> 00:16:43,164
As a matter of fact, it is. Yes.
事实上，倒是的

291
00:16:43,201 --> 00:16:46,602
Good, one less worry in the watches of the night.
很好，那晚上守夜时 可以少一点麻烦了

292
00:16:46,638 --> 00:16:48,572
Care for a cigar?
来根雪茄吗？

293
00:16:48,607 --> 00:16:50,734
No thank you, I don't smoke.
不，谢了，我不抽烟

294
00:16:50,776 --> 00:16:52,539
Oh this, yeah. That's...
哦，这个，这个是…

295
00:16:52,577 --> 00:16:55,011
in case nuclear war breaks out.
只是为了防止核战爆发

296
00:16:55,047 --> 00:16:56,207
I gave it up a long time ago.
我很早就戒烟了

297
00:16:56,248 --> 00:16:58,113
It's part habit, part superstition.
现在这样一半是因为习惯 一半是迷信

298
00:16:58,150 --> 00:16:59,515
It's, you know, a writer thing.
这是作家的通病

299
00:16:59,551 --> 00:17:01,314
You do drink, don't you?
那你一定喝酒吧？

300
00:17:01,353 --> 00:17:03,116
Of course, I just said I was a writer.
当然了，我刚说我是作家

301
00:17:03,155 --> 00:17:06,454
Le Cinquante Sept Deces, 1939.
１９３９年产的拉斯科威士忌

302
00:17:06,491 --> 00:17:08,288
Exquisite.
这可是上品

303
00:17:08,327 --> 00:17:10,522
About $800 a bottle, when you can find it.
如果你能买得到的话 大概是８００美元一瓶

304
00:17:10,562 --> 00:17:13,429
I appreciate the bribe, but I intend on staying in that room.
多谢你的贿赂 可我只想住在１４０８房

305
00:17:14,733 --> 00:17:16,792
- How long? - How long?
- 住多久？ - 多久？

306
00:17:17,803 --> 00:17:19,430
My usual is overnight.
通常情况下，我都是过夜

307
00:17:19,471 --> 00:17:21,439
I see.
我明白了

308
00:17:21,473 --> 00:17:24,306
No one's ever lasted more than an hour.
可从来没人在那房里捱过１小时

309
00:17:24,343 --> 00:17:26,277
(laughs) Jesus, man.
天啊，老兄

310
00:17:26,311 --> 00:17:28,370
You ought to shave your eyebrows and paint your hair gold
如果你是准备卖掉那狗屁的闹鬼房间

311
00:17:28,413 --> 00:17:30,904
if you're gonna try to sell that spookhouse bullshit.
你应该把你的眉毛剃了 然后染一头金发

312
00:17:30,949 --> 00:17:32,382
Otherwise, you'll scare the children.
否则你只能去吓吓小孩子

313
00:17:32,417 --> 00:17:34,476
Why are you mocking me when I am genuinely,
我正想方设法的帮你

314
00:17:34,519 --> 00:17:36,714
to the best of my ability, trying to help you?
你为什么却要嘲笑我呢？

315
00:17:36,755 --> 00:17:38,484
No, you're playing a little game.
不，你不过是在耍小把戏

316
00:17:38,523 --> 00:17:40,753
You're selling the mystique.
你是在故作高深

317
00:17:40,792 --> 00:17:43,192
But eventually, we both know
但是你我都清楚

318
00:17:43,228 --> 00:17:45,753
you're gonna give me the key and I'm gonna go up to the room
最后你还是会把钥匙给我 我还是会住进１４０８

319
00:17:45,797 --> 00:17:48,493
and I'm gonna write my story and your bookings are gonna go up 50%.
然后完成我的小说 而你的客房预定率也会随之上升五成

320
00:17:48,533 --> 00:17:51,866
Do you mind if my little friend records our conversation?
你不介意这位＂小朋友＂ 记录我们的谈话吧？

321
00:17:54,673 --> 00:17:56,072
I'll take that as a yes.
那我当你答应了？

322
00:17:56,108 --> 00:17:59,509
Sir, you quite misunderstand the situation.
先生，你完全低估了我们酒店

323
00:17:59,544 --> 00:18:02,843
Now, I know the Dolphin doesn't have the cachet of the Plaza
我知道海豚酒店没有广场酒店…

324
00:18:02,881 --> 00:18:04,576
or the Carlyle,
…或者卡莱尔酒店那么有名

325
00:18:04,616 --> 00:18:07,744
but we operate at 90% capacity.
但是我们总是保持 ９０％的客房入住率

326
00:18:07,786 --> 00:18:08,946
Always.
一直是

327
00:18:08,987 --> 00:18:11,649
And my concern here is not for the hotel.
我现在担心的不是酒店的前景

328
00:18:11,690 --> 00:18:14,215
My concern here is not for you.
也不是你个人的安危

329
00:18:14,259 --> 00:18:16,523
Frankly, selfishly,
坦白的讲，或者自私一点说

330
00:18:16,561 --> 00:18:19,530
I don't want you to check into 1408
我就是不想叫你入住１４０８房

331
00:18:19,564 --> 00:18:21,896
because I don't want to clean up the mess.
因为我不想去收拾你留下的烂摊子

332
00:18:21,933 --> 00:18:25,334
Now hotels are all about presentation
酒店经营重在自身形象

333
00:18:25,370 --> 00:18:27,930
and fertile creature comforts.
和提供良好的衣食住行服务

334
00:18:27,973 --> 00:18:30,942
My training is as a manager,
我学的是酒店管理

335
00:18:30,976 --> 00:18:32,944
not a coroner.
而不是验尸

336
00:18:32,978 --> 00:18:36,277
Under my watch there have been four deaths... four.
我已经亲眼目睹了 ４起死亡事件…４起啊

337
00:18:36,314 --> 00:18:38,874
After the last one, I forbade any guest
上次事件之后

338
00:18:38,917 --> 00:18:41,181
from checking into 1408 ever again.
我就禁止任何客人入住１４０８房

339
00:18:41,219 --> 00:18:44,552
The last one was David Hide, orthodontist, manic-depressive.
上次的死者叫大卫・海德 是个正牙医生，也是躁狂抑郁病患者

340
00:18:44,589 --> 00:18:46,716
Slit his wrist, did a little self-surgery,
他割腕自杀 在那之前给自己做了手术

341
00:18:46,758 --> 00:18:48,225
turned himself into a eunuch, right?
把自己阉了，我说得对吧？

342
00:18:48,260 --> 00:18:50,751
Yes. So you've done your homework.
没错，看来你还是做过些调查的

343
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:51,922
I'm a professional too.
我好歹也是职业作家

344
00:18:51,963 --> 00:18:54,864
Well, grievously, in its 95-year existence,
不幸的是，酒店成立的这９５年来

345
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:57,300
the hotel has seen seven jumpers,
已经发生过７起跳楼自杀

346
00:18:57,335 --> 00:18:59,360
four overdoses, five hangings,
４起服药过量死亡 ５起上吊

347
00:18:59,404 --> 00:19:00,632
- three mutilations... - Three mutilations...
- ３起自残身亡… - ３起自残身亡…

348
00:19:00,672 --> 00:19:02,367
two stranglings. General manager Gerald Olin
２起窒息死亡 盖瑞德・奥林总经理…

349
00:19:02,407 --> 00:19:04,534
is well-versed in the hotel's tragic history,
…很了解酒店历史上发生的悲剧

350
00:19:04,576 --> 00:19:07,374
dryly reciting the docket of carnage like a bookkeeper
讲述这些死亡事件时，很冷淡 就如同会计…

351
00:19:07,412 --> 00:19:09,141
discussing his ledger.
…谈论账目那般坦然自如

352
00:19:09,181 --> 00:19:11,240
Well, you think you're clever, don't you?
你以为自己很聪明，是吧？

353
00:19:11,283 --> 00:19:12,614
I know the game.
我知道你的伎俩

354
00:19:12,651 --> 00:19:14,050
Well, during your investigation,
在你的调查中

355
00:19:14,085 --> 00:19:16,576
did you discover the 22 natural deaths
有没有发现１４０８房曾发生过

356
00:19:16,621 --> 00:19:18,612
that have occurred in 1408?
２２起自然死亡事件？

357
00:19:20,392 --> 00:19:21,723
Natural deaths?
自然死亡

358
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:24,092
Ah, didn't find out about them
啊哈，不知道了吧

359
00:19:24,129 --> 00:19:27,656
because the newspapers don't print anything about them.
这些事报纸可没兴趣报道

360
00:19:27,699 --> 00:19:31,032
Hmm. All told, there have been 56 deaths
１４０８房总共发生过５６起死亡事件

361
00:19:31,069 --> 00:19:32,502
in 1408.
５６起？你耍我吧

362
00:19:32,537 --> 00:19:35,768
56? You're shitting me.

363
00:19:35,807 --> 00:19:37,604
You don't know anything.
看来你一点都不清楚

364
00:19:37,642 --> 00:19:40,668
The causes of death in 1408 range
１４０８房死者的死因五花八门

365
00:19:40,712 --> 00:19:43,146
from heart attack, stroke, drowning...
心脏病发作，中风 淹死…

366
00:19:43,181 --> 00:19:45,877
- Drowning? - Yes, one Mr. Grady Miller
- 淹死？ - 对，有位米勒先生

367
00:19:45,917 --> 00:19:48,044
drowned in his chicken soup.
淹死在鸡汤里

368
00:19:48,086 --> 00:19:50,452
That's hard to do. How... how did he do that?
这可不容易！ 他是怎么办到的？

369
00:19:50,489 --> 00:19:52,081
How indeed?
真的想知道？

370
00:19:52,123 --> 00:19:55,115
Interesting. It's all in here.
有意思吧 所有的记录都在这里

371
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:58,527
I will let you have this and give you access to my office.
我可以把这些资料给你 你也可以自由出入我办公室

372
00:19:58,563 --> 00:20:00,895
You can take notes, put it all in your book.
你可以做记录 把这些都写到你书里去

373
00:20:00,932 --> 00:20:03,127
My only condition
我只要求…

374
00:20:03,168 --> 00:20:06,865
is that you do not stay in that room.
…你不再要求入住１４０８房

375
00:20:06,905 --> 00:20:09,601
You'll let me look at all that stuff?
你会让我看所有这些资料？

376
00:20:09,641 --> 00:20:11,632
Hmm.
恩

377
00:20:19,351 --> 00:20:22,320
I never did get that drink.
我还没喝过那种酒

378
00:20:27,092 --> 00:20:28,491
(corks pops)

379
00:20:40,939 --> 00:20:44,272
- Oh, that is good. - Here, keep it.
- 哇，味道真不错 - 拿去吧

380
00:20:44,309 --> 00:20:46,334
Compliments of the house.
就算是酒店送你的礼物

381
00:20:57,956 --> 00:20:59,651
- I'm still staying. - Damn it to hell!
- 我还是要住那 - 他妈的！

382
00:20:59,691 --> 00:21:01,591
I'm sorry.
抱歉

383
00:21:01,626 --> 00:21:04,686
All right here. Here, read the godforsaken thing.
好吧 给，好好看看这些吧

384
00:21:04,729 --> 00:21:06,822
I guarantee you, once you've read it
我敢保证，读完之后

385
00:21:06,865 --> 00:21:09,231
you won't want to stay in 1408.
你肯定会改变主意不想住进１４０８

386
00:21:11,202 --> 00:21:13,466
The first victim: Mr. Kevin O'Malley,
第一位受害者 凯文・O・麦里先生

387
00:21:13,505 --> 00:21:15,302
sewing machine salesman.
是位缝纫机推销员

388
00:21:15,340 --> 00:21:17,205
Checked into the hotel the first week it opened...
于１９１２年１０月 酒店开业第一周入住…

389
00:21:17,242 --> 00:21:20,177
- October, 1912. - Cut his own throat, right?
他割喉而亡，对吗？

390
00:21:20,211 --> 00:21:21,769
Oh, that's not the horrific part.
那还不是最恐怖的

391
00:21:21,813 --> 00:21:23,838
Afterwards, in a fit of insanity,
之后，在流血身亡之前

392
00:21:23,882 --> 00:21:26,316
he tried to stitch himself back together
在近乎疯狂的状态下 他试图用老式的缝衣针…

393
00:21:26,351 --> 00:21:28,785
using an old sewing needle before he bled to death.
…把伤口再缝起来

394
00:21:28,820 --> 00:21:30,515
Easy, man.
放松点，老兄

395
00:21:30,555 --> 00:21:33,547
Look, Mr. Enslin, you don't have to stay in 1408.
听着，安斯林先生 你没必要住进１４０８房

396
00:21:33,592 --> 00:21:35,617
You can take photographs of 1404.
你完全可以在１４０４房拍些照片

397
00:21:35,660 --> 00:21:39,187
It has the exact same layout and no one will ever know the difference.
这２个房间布局完全一致 根本不会有人注意到有什么差别

398
00:21:39,230 --> 00:21:41,892
- My readers expect the truth. - Your readers?
- 可我的读者们想了解事实 - 你的读者？

399
00:21:41,933 --> 00:21:44,731
Your readers expect grotesqueries
你的读者们不过是想看些 荒诞离奇…

400
00:21:44,769 --> 00:21:46,930
and cheap thrills.
…廉价刺激的情节罢了

401
00:21:46,972 --> 00:21:49,702
"The headless ghost of Mr. Eugene Rilsby
＂无头鬼云格・李斯比…

402
00:21:49,741 --> 00:21:51,504
still walks his abandoned farmhouse."
…还是走进了废弃的农舍＂

403
00:21:51,543 --> 00:21:54,979
"The Barking Phantom of Mount Hope Cemetery."
＂霍普山墓地里咆哮的幽灵＂

404
00:21:55,013 --> 00:21:56,742
A direct quote... how'd you know that?
这些都是书中原话… 你是怎么知道的？

405
00:21:56,781 --> 00:21:58,544
Your books aren't hard to find.
你的书并不难找

406
00:21:58,583 --> 00:22:00,448
They're on the bargain shelves
每家书店的打折区都可以看到

407
00:22:00,485 --> 00:22:03,215
of any paperback novel store;

408
00:22:03,254 --> 00:22:06,781
full of cynicism, written by a talented, intelligent man
书中到处充斥着玩世不恭 而作者自称机敏过人，才华横溢

409
00:22:06,825 --> 00:22:09,487
who doesn't believe in anything or anyone but himself.
是个相当自负的人

410
00:22:09,527 --> 00:22:12,428
Guilty as charged.
随你怎么说吧

411
00:22:12,464 --> 00:22:15,262
Hey listen, this meeting's over. Why don't you give me the room?
我们没什么好谈的了 直接把房间钥匙给我吧

412
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:17,791
Oh please, don't act like a hurt schoolgirl.
别这样，别像个 受了委屈的小丫头似的

413
00:22:17,836 --> 00:22:20,896
- In fact, you surprised me. - Oh.
- 说实话，你还挺让我吃惊的 - 是吗？

414
00:22:20,939 --> 00:22:23,772
You are not the hack-n-slash I expected.
你并没有我想象的那么尖刻

415
00:22:23,808 --> 00:22:26,402
I rather liked the first one, the hardcover.
我真的挺喜欢你第一部小说 精装的那本

416
00:22:26,444 --> 00:22:30,141
What was it called? "The Last Walk..."
叫什么名字来着 ＂最后的散步…＂

417
00:22:30,181 --> 00:22:31,478
"Long Road Home."
＂漫漫回家路＂

418
00:22:31,516 --> 00:22:34,485
"The Long Road Home," yes.
＂漫漫回家路＂，就是这本

419
00:22:34,519 --> 00:22:36,987
I rather thought the father was a bastard.
我想那名父亲是个混蛋

420
00:22:37,022 --> 00:22:38,922
Yeah, he was.
是的，他的确是

421
00:22:38,957 --> 00:22:40,982
Um...
呃…

422
00:22:41,026 --> 00:22:42,493
Iook man, just give me the key.
老兄，快把钥匙给我吧

423
00:22:42,527 --> 00:22:45,621
- Mr. Enslin... - Just give me the key!
- 安斯林先生… - 快点给我钥匙！

424
00:22:45,664 --> 00:22:48,690
Listen, I stayed at the Bigsby house.
听着,我在皮戈比家住过

425
00:22:48,733 --> 00:22:51,668
I brushed my goddamn teeth right next to the tub
我还站在大卫・史密斯先生…

426
00:22:51,703 --> 00:22:54,001
where Sir David Smith drowned his whole family.
…淹死他一家老小的浴缸旁刷过牙

427
00:22:54,039 --> 00:22:57,008
And I stopped being afraid of vampires when I was 12.
我１２岁开始就不再怕吸血鬼了

428
00:22:57,042 --> 00:23:00,603
Do you know why I can stay in your spooky old room, Mr. Olin?
知道我为什么敢住你这 闹鬼的老屋吗，奥林先生？

429
00:23:00,645 --> 00:23:03,443
Because I know that ghoulies and ghosties
因为我知道鬼魂，幽灵

430
00:23:03,481 --> 00:23:05,779
and long-legged beasties don't exist.
这些东西根本就不存在

431
00:23:06,918 --> 00:23:08,408
Even if they did,
即使他们真的存在…

432
00:23:08,453 --> 00:23:11,047
there's no God to protect us from them, is there?
也没有神灵可以 保护我们不受伤害，对吗？

433
00:23:12,791 --> 00:23:14,782
So I can't talk you out of this?
我根本就不可能说服你，是吗？

434
00:23:14,826 --> 00:23:17,386
I think we've reached an understanding.
我想我们都彼此清楚

435
00:23:17,429 --> 00:23:19,863
Very well.
那好吧

436
00:23:19,898 --> 00:23:22,458
Come with me.
跟我来

437
00:23:27,439 --> 00:23:29,532
(jangles)

438
00:23:32,610 --> 00:23:34,271
(elevator dings)

439
00:23:34,312 --> 00:23:36,746
Most hotels have switched to magnetics.
大多数酒店早就改成磁卡钥匙了

440
00:23:36,781 --> 00:23:40,217
An actual key. That's a nice touch... it's antiquey.
那房间居然还使用这么原始钥匙 手感很不错…古色古香的

441
00:23:40,251 --> 00:23:43,812
We have magnetic cards also, but electronics don't seem to work in 1408.
我们有磁卡钥匙，但是 电子设备在１４０８房似乎不能工作

442
00:23:43,855 --> 00:23:45,720
Hope you don't have a pacemaker.
希望你身上没有心脏起博器

443
00:23:45,757 --> 00:23:48,726
General manager claims that the phantom in room interferes...
总经理宣称房间里的幽灵干扰…

444
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:50,853
I have never used the word "phantom."
我可从来没提过＂幽灵＂这词

445
00:23:50,895 --> 00:23:53,363
Oh, I'm sorry. Spirit? Specter?
抱歉，那＂灵魂＂呢？ 或者＂妖怪＂？

446
00:23:53,398 --> 00:23:54,922
No, you misunderstand.
不，你误会了

447
00:23:54,966 --> 00:23:57,230
Whatever's in 1408 is nothing like that.
１４０８房不会有这些东西的

448
00:23:57,268 --> 00:24:00,066
Then what is it?
那么是什么？

449
00:24:00,105 --> 00:24:02,539
It's an evil fucking room.
就是间他妈的邪恶的房间

450
00:24:04,476 --> 00:24:06,603
Please.
请上电梯吧

451
00:24:10,348 --> 00:24:13,943
Mr. Odin. (speaks French)
奥林先生 能帮我签下字吗？

452
00:24:13,985 --> 00:24:16,783
Oh, oui. Tres bien.
- 好的 - 谢谢

453
00:24:18,590 --> 00:24:20,182
(classical music playing)

454
00:24:22,260 --> 00:24:24,785
Why don't the owners just close the room?
酒店老板为什么不关闭那房间呢？

455
00:24:26,464 --> 00:24:28,932
The Yasuko Corporation prefers to pretend there's no problem.
酒店的领导层更希望装做 一切都不曾发生过

456
00:24:28,967 --> 00:24:31,959
Just as they pretend there's no 13th floor.
就好像假装没有１３楼一样

457
00:24:33,605 --> 00:24:35,573
The room, it's got to be filthy.
那房间一定很脏吧？

458
00:24:35,607 --> 00:24:37,802
I mean, the sheets haven't been changed in what? 11 years?
床单应该有…１１年没换洗过了吧？

459
00:24:37,842 --> 00:24:40,777
No no no, we're very professional.
不，不， 我们酒店可专业呢

460
00:24:40,812 --> 00:24:44,248
1408 gets a light turn once a month.
我们每个月都会简单打扫下１４０８房

461
00:24:44,282 --> 00:24:46,512
I supervise, the maids work in pairs.
由我亲自监督 ２名清洁女工结伴打扫的

462
00:24:46,551 --> 00:24:49,315
We treat the room as if it's a chamber
每次打扫房间 都像是打扫充满毒气的毒气室一样

463
00:24:49,354 --> 00:24:50,878
filled with poison gas.

464
00:24:50,922 --> 00:24:54,619
We only stay 10 minutes and I insist the door remain open.
打扫不会超过１０分钟 而且我坚持一定要把房门打开

465
00:24:54,659 --> 00:24:57,025
But still...
可还是…

466
00:24:59,330 --> 00:25:01,958
A few years ago, a young maid from El Salvador
几年前，一个萨尔瓦多藉的年轻女工

467
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,558
found herself locked in the bathroom.
被锁在卫生间里

468
00:25:03,601 --> 00:25:04,829
She was only there for a few moments,
虽然时间不长

469
00:25:04,869 --> 00:25:06,860
but when we pulled her out, she was...
但是当她出来时，她…

470
00:25:06,905 --> 00:25:09,635
- She was dead. - No, blind.
- 死了？ - 错，是瞎了

471
00:25:09,674 --> 00:25:11,869
She had taken a pair of scissors
她用剪子…

472
00:25:11,910 --> 00:25:13,878
and gouged her eyes out.
…把自己的眼珠挖了出来

473
00:25:13,912 --> 00:25:16,278
- She was laughing hysterically. - (bell rings)
而且还歇斯底里的不停狂笑

474
00:25:16,314 --> 00:25:18,612
- Ouch. - Your floor.
我们到了

475
00:25:19,784 --> 00:25:21,411
Well, this is where we part company.
我只能陪你到这里

476
00:25:21,452 --> 00:25:24,683
This is as close as I get to 1408
除非每个月打扫房间

477
00:25:24,722 --> 00:25:26,781
unless it's that time of the month.
否则我不愿靠近１４０８房半步

478
00:25:28,693 --> 00:25:31,423
- See you tomorrow. - Mr. Enslin?
- 那就明天见了 - 安斯林先生？

479
00:25:31,462 --> 00:25:33,430
Please...
求你…

480
00:25:33,464 --> 00:25:35,432
don't do this.
…别进去

481
00:25:38,670 --> 00:25:40,638
I'll call you about those Knicks tickets.
我会来电话联系你 尼克斯队比赛门票的事

482
00:25:40,672 --> 00:25:43,197
(bell rings)

483
00:25:55,587 --> 00:25:57,885
(man speaking loudly)

484
00:26:13,171 --> 00:26:15,332
(TV playing)

485
00:26:17,842 --> 00:26:19,469
(wheel squeaking)

486
00:26:29,888 --> 00:26:31,981
(woman laughing) Stop it!

487
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:44,698
(elevator dings)

488
00:26:44,736 --> 00:26:47,569
(classical music playing)

489
00:26:51,639 --> 00:26:54,639
[我哥在康涅狄格州收费公路上 被狼群吃了]

490
00:27:04,088 --> 00:27:06,056
(flies buzzing)

491
00:27:06,090 --> 00:27:08,251
(baby crying)

492
00:27:10,962 --> 00:27:13,795
Okay. It's okay, sweetie. We're home now.
好了，宝贝 我们到家了

493
00:27:13,831 --> 00:27:14,923
Here we go.
我们进去吧

494
00:27:21,306 --> 00:27:23,171
(knocks)

495
00:28:19,731 --> 00:28:21,858
This is it?
就这样？

496
00:28:22,867 --> 00:28:25,529
You got to be kidding me.
开玩笑吧？

497
00:28:41,519 --> 00:28:44,818
Round one goes to the hideous Mr. Olin for effective aggressiveness.
第一轮，讨厌的奥林先生 运用他有效攻势先发制人

498
00:28:44,856 --> 00:28:48,189
I have to admit, he had me going for a moment.
不得不承认 我差点就被他的阵势给唬住

499
00:28:49,460 --> 00:28:52,293
But where is the bone-chilling terror?
但是那令人毛骨悚然的 恐怖场面在哪？

500
00:28:52,330 --> 00:28:55,094
Show me the rivers of blood.
血流成河的场景在哪儿呢？

501
00:29:01,072 --> 00:29:03,540
It's just a room.
这不过是间普通的房间罢了

502
00:29:03,574 --> 00:29:05,701
(Muzak playing)

503
00:29:07,274 --> 00:29:07,701
［成人节目］

504
00:29:08,852 --> 00:29:09,613
［春假，纵欲主妇，放荡野樱桃］

505
00:29:14,952 --> 00:29:16,613
(TV turns off)

506
00:29:19,614 --> 00:29:20,614
［圣经］

507
00:29:48,453 --> 00:29:51,718
$8 for beer nuts.
开胃豆８美圆

508
00:29:51,756 --> 00:29:54,281
This room is evil.
这房间确实邪恶

509
00:29:54,325 --> 00:29:57,385
Mike's voice: Olin said hotels are about fertile creature comforts.
奥林说酒店经营在于 良好的服务

510
00:29:57,428 --> 00:29:59,726
It's a good line, but I wonder
这话说的漂亮 但是我怀疑…

511
00:29:59,764 --> 00:30:02,562
whether they're really about reassuring platitudes,
…他指的究竟是不是 眼前的这些…

